# Cursor IDE — Cinematic Drama Agent Queue Orchestrator

This repo is the dedicated workspace for AI agents writing Cinematic Drama
stories for the Source2Draft → Agent Queue API (`hlagency.net`, happykitemedia
WebApp). It is not the WebApp codebase — only guides, helper scripts, and
per-runtime entrypoints live here.

## Read first

1. `docs/guides/CINEMATIC_DRAMA_EXTERNAL_AGENT.md` — full spec: API, 7-stage
   pipeline, Revision/Social-Kit modes, quality standards, Writer/Critic
   pattern. Authoritative; this file is only a Cursor-specific operational
   summary of it.
2. `docs/guides/AGENT_KICKOFF_PROMPTS.md` §2 ("Cursor IDE Agent") for the full
   kickoff prompt this file summarizes.

## Runtime constraint

Cursor IDE has **no subagent spawn tool and no cron**. You play both roles
sequentially in the same session, strictly separated:

- **Writer role**: draft `task_<id>/{title,fb,comment,website,image_prompt}.txt`
  + `character_sheet.json` following `data.input.instructions` (7 stages, in
  order). Never grade your own draft.
- **Critic role**: judge the **files only** — never your own drafting
  reasoning. Run `python3 docs/guides/cinematic_qc.py task_<id>/` as a hard
  gate first, then score the rubric (`TOTAL ≥ 80`, `fb_hook ≥ 17`,
  `comment_pull ≥ 13` → PASS; else fix the 2 lowest dimensions, max 3 soft
  rounds, best-of ≥ 70 fallback).

One story at a time. Submit only after the Critic role returns PASS or
best-of.

## Hard rules

- **Do NOT edit any repository files** as your task output — your only
  outputs are files under `/tmp/agy_scratch` and API calls. (Editing the
  guides/scripts themselves, when the user explicitly asks you to update this
  repo, is fine — this rule is about story-writing task output.)
- Never print task JSON or full story text into the terminal — files +
  `python3` only (large source transcripts get truncated otherwise).
- Never commit or paste a real `AQ_KEY` / `sk_ag_...` into any file. Export it
  as a shell env var only.
- HARD 60-minute timeout from claim (up to 75 min with an active heartbeat —
  a recent heartbeat buys up to 15 min of grace, but never rely on it;
  finish well under 60 min). `POST /<id>/heartbeat` regularly.

## Credentials

```bash
export AQ_BASE="https://hlagency.net/api/n8n/agent-queue"
export AQ_KEY="sk_ag_..."
export AQ_AGENT="<MACHINE_ID>-Cursor-orchestrator-1"
mkdir -p /tmp/agy_scratch
```

## Revision batches

For bulk `revision_note` queues (mechanical fixes, no fresh 7-step write), use
`docs/guides/AGENT_KICKOFF_PROMPTS.md` §3a and
`scripts/agent-worker/process_one_revision.sh` /
`process_revision_batch.sh`.
